# Verification

Run the smallest relevant verification that proves the change. Full harness: `docs/verification-harness.md`.

| Change | Verification |
|---|---|
| Logic | Unit test |
| Flow | Integration test |
| Typed code | Typecheck |
| Frontend/package | Build |
| Schema | Migration validation |
| CLI/runtime | Smoke run |
| Bug fix | Reproduce → test → fix → retest |
| Aion task | Use Aion session status + final report + project tests |

Inspect verifier signals before inventing commands: `package.json`, `pyproject.toml`, `Cargo.toml`, `go.mod`, `Makefile`.

Anti-stuck: do not rerun the same failing command more than 2 times without a new hypothesis. Max 3 fix-and-retest loops, then report `BLOCKED`.

Anti-overmocking: prefer behavior/integration tests. Mock only external boundaries: network, filesystem, clock, paid APIs, hardware, external services.

Debug escalation: after 2 failed fix loops without new evidence, add logging/instrumentation or inspect a different layer. Stop guessing at the same edit site.

Never say tests passed if they were not run.
